  schema:name "Armed Joy" ;
  schema:description "Bonanno's concept: the experience of freedom in the act of resistance itself — not the anticipation of victory or the satisfaction of a goal achieved, but the intensity of present-tense action against domination, in which the boundary between struggle and life dissolves." ;
